      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear how incredibly heavy and exhausting this feels, especially after six years of pouring everything into a project. It makes complete sense that you're feeling a sense of emptiness and failure right now. When you've invested that much time and energy, the loss of results or funding can feel like a personal collapse, even if it's just a setback.\n\nIt's okay to feel tired of the loop. You don't have to fix everything right this second. Sometimes, just acknowledging that you're struggling and that it's okay to step back for a moment is the most important thing you can do. You haven't failed anyone; you've just hit a difficult wall, and that doesn't define your worth or your future.",
